               <head>Astrological treatise</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Lavā’iḥ al-qamar by Kāshifī, Ḥusayn Vāʻiẓ, d. 1504 or 5</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2001000141" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15656-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_90770167">Kāshifī, Ḥusayn Vāʻiẓ, d. 1504 or 5</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="viaf_90770167" type="supplied">كاشفي، حسين واعظ</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22060">Lavā’iḥ al-qamar</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22060">لوائح القمر</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>An astrological treatise, concerning auspicious hours, days and months according to the positions of the moon by Ḥusayn Vā‘iẓ Kāshifī (d. 910/1504-5). </p>
                        <p>The present manuscript was produced during the author’s lifetime and probably in his hometown of Herat, and strengthens the case for using the alternative title of the work, <title>Ikhtiyārāt-i	nujūm</title>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work contains a number of tables.</p>
                        <p>Colophon on title page, f. 1r, naming the work as Ikhtiyārāt al-nujūm and the author as Ustāz̲unā va Shaykhunā al-Ḥakīm Ḥusayn bin ‘Alī al-Bayhaqī al-Kashifī al-Haravī. Copied in Muḥarram 909/June-July 1503 by ‘Alī ibn Muḥammad al-Mashhadī al-Haravī.</p>
                        <p>Other contents: f. 1r, inscription giving the title as Ikhtiyārāt al-nujūm; later small inscription: Ikhtiyārāt-i nujūm va Risālah dar ma‘rifat-i istikhrāj-i taqvīm; ownership inscription of Aḥmad ibn Faz̤l Allāh al-Shīrāzī, 1000/1591-2.</p>
                        <p>Title supplied. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation />
